Issues.Body:
This is about the Bulma Notification 
I'm using Bulma 0.8.0
My Browser is Chrome Version 81.0.4044.129

### Description

When I create multiple notification box, only one could be closed.

The others stay.

My solution:

https://bulma.io/documentation/elements/notification/

changed

```
document.addEventListener('DOMContentLoaded', () => {
  (document.querySelectorAll('.notification .delete') || []).forEach(($delete) => {
    $notification = $delete.parentNode;

    $delete.addEventListener('click', () => {
      $notification.parentNode.removeChild($notification);
    });
  });
});
```

with

```
document.addEventListener('DOMContentLoaded', () => {
  (document.querySelectorAll('.notification .delete') || []).forEach(($delete) => {
    $delete.addEventListener('click', () => {
	  $delete.parentNode.remove();
    });
  });
});
```

i feel that is better,
